    {215, kDeckId, "disclose", "[dɪs'kloz]", "v. 揭示；泄露；公开；揭露", "1. Some companies have already voluntarily disclosed similar information .\n   一些公司已经主动透露了类似的信息。\n2. He refused to disclose the identity of the politician.\n   他拒绝透露那位政治家的身份。", ""},
    {216, kDeckId, "enclose", "[ɪn'kloz]", "v. 围住；圈起；封入；围绕；装入；放入封套；封入 <", "1. The pool area is enclosed by a six-foot wall.\n   游泳区用六英尺高的高墙围了起来。\n2. Please enclose a cheque with your order.\n   请随订单附上支票。", ""},
    {217, kDeckId, "enclosure", "[ɪn'kloʒɚ]", "n. 围住；圈起；封入；附件；围墙；围场；四周有篱笆的场地", "1. the enclosure of arable land for pasture\n   将耕地圈起来用作牧场\n2. the bear enclosure at the zoo\n   动物园中的熊园", ""},
