    {241, kDeckId, "decrease", "[dɪ'kris]", "n. 减少；减小；减少量\nv. 减少；变少；降低；减小", "1. They want to decrease their reliance on oil.\n   他们想减少对石油的依赖。\n2. The number of people who have the disease has decreased significantly in recent years.\n   近年来，这种病的患者人数明显下降。", ""},
    {242, kDeckId, "discreet", "[dɪ'skrit]", "adj. (言行)谨慎的；慎重的；有判断力的；谨慎的；小心的", "1. He assured her that he would be discreet.\n   他向她保证会谨慎行事。\n2. I stood back at a discreet distance.\n   我谨慎地保持一段距离站在后面。", ""},
