    {290, kDeckId, "predict", "[prɪ'dɪkt]", "v. 预言；预测；预告；预报；预知", "1. As Liz had predicted , the rumours were soon forgotten.\n   正如利兹所预料的，流言很快就被淡忘了。\n2. Sales were five percent lower than predicted.\n   销售额比预期低5%。", ""},
    {291, kDeckId, "dedicate", "['dɛdɪket]", "v. 奉献；献身于；致力；献身；题献；把…用在", "1. For the next few years, she dedicated herself to her work.\n   随后的几年里，她全身心地投入工作。\n2. She dedicated her first album to Woody Allen, who she says understands her obsession.\n   她把她的第一张唱片献给伍迪·艾伦，她说艾伦理解她的痴迷。", ""},
    {292, kDeckId, "indicate", "['ɪndɪket]", "v. 指出；指示；表明；暗示；预示；象征；指示 A；表明或暗示…的可能性 A", "1. The study indicates a connection between poverty and crime.\n   研究显示贫穷和犯罪有关联。", ""},
    {293, kDeckId, "indication", "[,ɪndɪ'keʃən]", "n. 指出；指示；表明；暗示；迹象；象征", "1. Indications are that the situation hasn't improved much.\n   迹象表明局势并没有多大好转。\n2. Could you give me some indication as to when I am likely to receive a reply?\n   你能给我透露一下什么时候我能收到回复吗？", ""},
