    {402, kDeckId, "former", "['fɔrmɚ]", "adj. 以前的；在前的\npron. 前者", "1. Of the two possibilities, the former seems more likely.\n   在这两种可能性中，前者似乎更有可能。\n2. Their farm has been reduced to half its former size.\n   他们的农场已缩小到以前的一半。", ""},
    {403, kDeckId, "formidable", "['fɔrmɪdəbl]", "adj. 强大的；令人敬畏的；可怕的；艰难的；令人敬畏的 A <；难以应付的", "1. The new range of computers have formidable processing power.\n   该系列的新型计算机处理能力惊人。\n2. The building is grey, formidable, not at all picturesque.\n   那幢建筑呈灰色，气势凛然，与漂亮沾不上边。", ""},
