    {446, kDeckId, "indignation", "[,ɪndɪɡ'neʃən]", "n. 愤怒；愤慨；义愤", "1. He stormed into her office, full of righteous indignation.\n   他义愤填膺，气呼呼地冲进她的办公室。\n2. To his indignation, Charles found that his name was not on the list.\n   查尔斯发现他的名字没有出现在名单上，这让他深感愤慨。", ""},
