    {597, kDeckId, "mankind", "[mæn'kaɪnd]", "n. 人类；男性；人类 A", "1. Since earliest times, mankind has been fascinated by fire.\n   人类自远古以来就对火很感兴趣。\n2. one of the most important events in the history of mankind\n   人类历史上最重要的事件之一", ""},
    {598, kDeckId, "manner", "['mænɚ]", "n. 方式；举止；(pl.)风度；礼貌；规矩；风俗；习惯；种类；方法", "1. The issue will be resolved in a manner that is fair to both sides.\n   这个问题将用对双方都公平的方式来解决。\n2. He felt some guilt over the manner of her death.\n   她以这种方式死去，他心里有些内疚。", ""},
    {599, kDeckId, "permanent", "['pɝmənənt]", "adj. 永久的；持久的；永恒的；不变的\nn. 烫发（等于permanent wave）", "1. The blindness that the disease causes will be permanent.\n   这种疾病引起的失明是永久性的。\n2. He gave up a permanent job in order to freelance.\n   他放弃了固定工作，为的是当一名自由职业者。", ""},
    {600, kDeckId, "policeman", "[pə'lismən]", "n. 警察", "1. I think he must be a policeman, he keeps fishing for information.\n   我想他肯定是警察，他不断地转弯抹角地打听消息。\n2. The thief withered under the stare of the policeman.\n   小偷在警察的逼视下显得惶恐不安。", ""},
    {601, kDeckId, "postman", "['postmən]", "n. 邮递员；邮差", "1. The old man often stands here to watch out for the postman.\n   老人常常站在这儿等邮递员。\n2. That postman is in charge of this route.\n   那个邮递员负责这条投递线路。", ""},
    {602, kDeckId, "romance", "[ro'mæns]", "n. 传奇；爱情故事；浪漫史；风流韵事；冒险故事\nv. 虚构；渲染；写传奇", "1. Michelle married him after a whirlwind romance .\n   经过一场旋风式的恋爱，米歇尔嫁给了他。\n2. The romance had gone out of their relationship.\n   他们之间已经没有了爱意。", ""},
    {603, kDeckId, "romantic", "[ro'mæntɪk]", "adj. 浪漫的；传奇式的；不切实际的；好幻想的；多情的；空想的\nn. 浪漫的人\nv. 使…浪漫化", "1. 'Tom always sends me red roses on my birthday.' 'How romantic!'\n   \"我过生日时汤姆总是给我送红玫瑰。\"\"多浪漫啊！\"", ""},
