    {896, kDeckId, "position", "[pə'zɪʃən]", "n. 位置；职位；姿势；姿态；见解；立场；形势；方位；工作；站位\nv. 安置；把……放在适当位置", "1. Frankie shifted his position so that his knees would not become cramped.\n   弗朗基换了个姿势，这样他的膝盖就不会老蜷着动弹不得。\n2. Lie in a comfortable position .\n   以一个舒服的姿势躺下。", ""},
    {897, kDeckId, "positive", "['pɑzətɪv]", "adj. 肯定的；积极的；绝对的；无疑的；正的；[数] 正的；[医][化学] 阳性的；确定的；实际的；真实的；肯定的 <；确实的；明确的；〈美〉...", "1. At least something positive has come out of the situation.\n   至少这个情况也产生了一些积极的东西。\n2. Write down all the positive things about your life.\n   记下生活中所有好的事情。", ""},
    {898, kDeckId, "preposition", "[,prɛpə'zɪʃən]", "n. 介词；前置词", "1. There is nothing in the rules of grammar to suggest that ending a sentence with a preposition is wrong.\n   在语法规则中没有哪一条表明以介词结束一个句子是错误的。", ""},
    {899, kDeckId, "proposal", "[prə'pozl]", "n. 提议；建议；求婚", "1. The president is to put forward new proposals for resolving the country's constitutional crisis.\n   总统将提出解决国家宪法危机的新议案。", ""},
    {900, kDeckId, "propose", "[prə'poz]", "v. 提议；建议；提名；推荐；求婚；打算；计划", "1. He proposed to his girlfriend over a public-address system.\n   他在有线广播系统上向女友求婚。\n2. the changes currently proposed by the local planning authorities\n   目前由地方规划局提议的改革", ""},
