    {905, kDeckId, "possess", "[pə'zɛs]", "v. 占有；拥有；控制；使掌握；持有；迷住；具备", "1. He no longer possessed the power to frighten her.\n   他再也吓不倒她了。\n2. Different workers possess different skills.\n   不同的工人拥有不同技能。", ""},
    {906, kDeckId, "possession", "[pə'zɛʃən]", "n. 持有；拥有；所有权；所有物；(pl.)财产；财富；财产；领地；自制；着迷", "1. How did the painting come into your possession ?\n   这幅画是怎么到你手上的？\n2. The finance company now has possession of the house.\n   这家金融公司目前拥有这所房子。", ""},
    {907, kDeckId, "possibility", "[,pɑsə'bɪləti]", "n. 可能；可能性；可能的事；希望；可能发生的事物", "1. There's always a possibility that he might go back to Seattle.\n   他也许会回到西雅图去，这种可能性一直存在。\n2. There was no possibility of changing the voting procedure.\n   改变投票程序是不可能的。", ""},
    {908, kDeckId, "possible", "['pɑsəbl]", "adj. 可能的；做得到的；合理的；可允许的；合适的\nn. 可能性；合适的人；可能的事物", "1. We are doing everything possible to track down the killer.\n   我们正竭尽全力追捕杀人凶手。\n2. She decided to stay as far away from him as was humanly possible .\n   她决定尽可能离他远点。", ""},
    {909, kDeckId, "possibly", "['pɑsəbli]", "adv. 可能地；也许；无论如何；大概", "1. This last task is possibly the most difficult.\n   这最后一项任务也许是最难的。\n2. It will take three weeks, possibly longer.\n   要花三个星期，也许更久。", ""},
