    {1194, kDeckId, "customer", "['kʌstəmɚ]", "n. 顾客；主顾；家伙", "1. We aim to offer good value and service to all our customers.\n   我们力求为所有的客户提供物有所值的商品和服务。\n2. We've had several letters from satisfied customers.\n   我们收到了几封顾客表示满意的来信。", ""},
    {1195, kDeckId, "tomato", "[tə'meto]", "n. 西红柿；番茄", "1. He staked his tomato vines with bamboo.\n   他用竹竿支撑起西红柿秧。\n2. The salmon was brought to the table whole, garnished with parsley and slices of tomato and cucumber.\n   整条大麻哈鱼被端上了桌，并用欧芹、西红柿片和黄瓜片作为花色配菜。", ""},
