    {1227, kDeckId, "conventional", "[kən'vɛnʃənl]", "adj. 惯例的；常规的；符合习俗的；传统的；常见的", "1. Bake for 20 minutes in a conventional oven; 8 in a microwave.\n   在传统的烤炉中烘烤20分钟，在微波炉里则烤8分钟。\n2. Internet connections through conventional phone lines are fairly slow.\n   通过传统的电话线来连接因特网速度很慢。", ""},
    {1228, kDeckId, "event", "[ɪ'vɛnt]", "n. 事件；事情", "1. one of the most important events in the history of mankind\n   人类历史上最重大的事件之一", ""},
    {1229, kDeckId, "eventually", "[ɪ'vɛntʃuəli]", "adv. 终于；最后", "1. He eventually escaped and made his way back to England.\n   他终于逃脱并返回英格兰。\n2. Eventually, she got a job and moved to London.\n   最终，她找到了工作并移居伦敦。", ""},
    {1230, kDeckId, "intervene", "[,ɪntɚ'vin]", "v. (in)干涉；干预；插入；介入；干涉；调停；插手", "1. The army will have to intervene to prevent further fighting.\n   军队将不得不干预以阻止进一步的战斗。", ""},
