    {1325, kDeckId, "revive", "[rɪ'vaɪv]", "v. 恢复；(使)复苏；复兴；复活；苏醒；恢复精神；复苏 <", "1. Local people have decided to revive this centuries-old tradition.\n   当地人决定复兴这一延续了数个世纪的传统。\n2. The doctors revived her with injections of glucose.\n   医生给她注射葡萄糖，使她苏醒过来。", ""},
    {1326, kDeckId, "survival", "[sɚ'vaɪvl]", "n. 幸存；生存；幸存者；残存物；残存", "1. A lot of small companies are having to fight for survival .\n   很多小公司不得不挣扎求生。\n2. The doctors gave him a one in ten chance of survival .\n   医生说他有十分之一的生存希望。", ""},
    {1327, kDeckId, "survive", "[sɚ'vaɪv]", "v. 幸免于；幸存；比…长命；生还；比活得长", "1. Only 12 of the 140 passengers survived.\n   140 名乘客中只有 12 人生还。\n2. Those organisms that are most suited to the environment will be those that will survive.\n   那些最适应环境的生物将是那些存活下来的。", ""},
