    {1442, kDeckId, "belief", "[bɪ'lif]", "n. 相信；信赖；信仰；教义；信条 A；信念", "1. When you get something wrong, it can shake your belief in yourself.\n   如果有什么事情没做好，就会动摇你对自己的信心。", ""},
    {1443, kDeckId, "spend", "[spɛnd]", "v. 度过；消磨（时光）；花费；浪费；用尽\nn. 预算", "1. I can't afford to spend any more money this week.\n   这星期我没有能力花更多的钱了。\n2. The repairs cost a lot, but it's money well spent .\n   修理费很高，但这是该花的钱。", ""},
    {1444, kDeckId, "necessary", "[ˈnɛsəˌsɛri]", "adj. 必要的；必需的；必然的\nn. 必需品", "1. The doctor says it may be necessary for me to have an operation.\n   医生说我可能需要做手术。\n2. The booklet provides all the necessary information about the college.\n   这本小册子提供了关于那所学院的所有必需信息。", ""},
    {1445, kDeckId, "network", "['nɛtwɝk]", "n. 网络；广播网；网状物；电视网；网络 A", "1. Hungary's telephone network\n   匈牙利的电话网\n2. a high-speed European rail network\n   欧洲的高速铁路网", ""},
    {1446, kDeckId, "organization", "[,ɔrɡənə'zeʃən]", "n. 组织；机构；体制；团体；结构", "1. The public expect high standards from any large organization.\n   公众对任何大型机构都期望很高。\n2. a voluntary organization which helps disabled people with their transport needs\n   帮助残疾人士满足其交通需求的一个志愿组织", ""},
