    {1484, kDeckId, "pattern", "['pætɚn]", "n. 模式；图案；样品；图样；式样\nv. 模仿；以图案装饰；仿制", "1. The exam system is patterned after the one used in Japan.\n   这种考试制度是仿效日本建立的。\n2. Their descriptions seemed to follow a set pattern .\n   他们的描述似乎依据固定的模式。", ""},
    {1485, kDeckId, "ignore", "[ɪɡ'nɔr]", "v. 驳回诉讼；忽视；不理睬", "1. You can't ignore the fact that many criminals never go to prison.\n   你不能无视很多罪犯从未获刑的事实。\n2. problems which we can't afford to ignore\n   我们不能置之不理的问题", ""},
    {1486, kDeckId, "flow", "[flo]", "v. 流动；涌流；川流不息；飘扬\nn. 流动；流量；涨潮；泛滥", "1. Money has been flowing into the country from Western aid agencies.\n   资金源源不断地从西方援助机构流入该国。", ""},
    {1487, kDeckId, "suitable", "['sutəbl]", "adj. 适当的；相配的", "1. We are hoping to find a suitable school.\n   我们希望能找到一所合适的学校。", ""},
    {1488, kDeckId, "environment", "[ɪn'vaɪrənmənt]", "n. 环境；外界", "1. Some of these chemicals are very damaging to the environment.\n   这些化学品中有些对环境非常有害。\n2. the effects of acid rain on the environment\n   酸雨对环境的影响", ""},
    {1489, kDeckId, "exercise", "['ɛksɚsaɪz]", "n. 运动；练习；运用；操练；礼拜；典礼\nv. 锻炼；练习；使用；使忙碌；使惊恐", "1. Try to fit some regular exercise into your daily routine.\n   尽量在日常生活中安排一些经常性的锻炼。\n2. Working in an office, I don't get much exercise.\n   由于在办公室工作，我很少运动。", ""},
    {1490, kDeckId, "force", "[fɔrs]", "n. 力量；武力；军队；魄力\nv. 促使；推动；强迫；强加", "1. The UN will allow the use of force against aircraft violating the zone.\n   联合国将允许对侵犯这一地区的飞机采取军事行动。\n2. Peace cannot be imposed by force .\n   和平不能通过武力来实现。", ""},
    {1491, kDeckId, "personal", "['pɝsənl]", "adj. 个人的；身体的；亲自的\nn. 人事消息栏；人称代名词", "1. She took full personal responsibility for all the arrangements.\n   她个人对所有的安排承担全部责任。\n2. When I went to her room all her personal belongings had gone.\n   我到她房间时，她所有的私人物品都已不在了。", ""},
