    {3739, kDeckId, "nearby", "[,nɪr'baɪ]", "adj. 附近的；邻近的\nadv. 在附近\nprep. 在…附近", "1. He might easily have been seen by someone who lived nearby.\n   他可能很容易被住在附近的人看到。\n2. Lucy was staying in the nearby town of Hamilton.\n   露西当时住在附近的汉密尔顿镇。", ""},
    {3740, kDeckId, "irritate", "['ɪrɪtet]", "v. 刺激；使兴奋；激怒；使恼火；使急躁；刺激 A", "1. It really irritates me when he doesn't help around the house.\n   家里的事情他一点都不帮忙，真让我恼火。", ""},
