    {4822, kDeckId, "rare", "[rɛr]", "adj. 稀有的；难得的；珍奇的；稀薄的；稀疏的", "1. I only saw Helen on the rare occasions when I went into her shop.\n   我只有偶尔去海伦店里时才会见到她。\n2. This species of plant is becoming increasingly rare.\n   这种植物越来越罕见。", ""},
    {4823, kDeckId, "fatigued", "[fə'tiɡd]", "adj. 疲乏的", "1. Sara looked white and fatigued.\n   萨拉看上去脸色苍白，精疲力竭。", ""},
    {4824, kDeckId, "rehearse", "[rɪ'hɝs]", "v. 排练；预演", "1. I think we need to rehearse the first scene again.\n   我想我们需要把第一场再排练一次。", ""},
    {4825, kDeckId, "flourish", "[ˈflɜːrɪʃ]", "v. 繁荣；茂盛；兴旺", "1. The economy is booming and small businesses are flourishing.\n   经济繁荣，小企业蒸蒸日上。", ""},
    {4826, kDeckId, "likely", "['laɪkli]", "adv. 大概；多半 A\nadj. 很可能的；有希望的", "1. It is more than likely the votes will have to be counted again.\n   选票很有可能要重新点算。\n2. It could have been an accident, but that was hardly likely .\n   这有可能是意外事故，但可能性不大。", ""},
    {4827, kDeckId, "brittle", "['brɪtl]", "adj. 易碎的；脆的", "1. Joanna was diagnosed as having brittle bones.\n   乔安娜被诊断为骨质疏松。\n2. The branches were dry and brittle.\n   那些树枝又干又脆。", ""},
    {4828, kDeckId, "dependence", "[dɪ'pɛndəns]", "n. 依靠；依赖；信任", "1. the city's traditional dependence on tourism.\n   …这个城市对旅游业的传统依赖。", ""},
    {4829, kDeckId, "ability", "[əˈbɪlətɪ]", "n. 能力；智能", "1. The test measures your mathematical ability.\n   这种测试考查的是数学能力。", ""},
    {4830, kDeckId, "orchestra", "['ɔrkɪstrə]", "n. 管弦乐队", "1. the Berlin Symphony Orchestra\n   柏林交响乐团\n2. the school orchestra\n   校管弦乐队", ""},
    {4831, kDeckId, "claim", "[klem]", "v. 要求；主张；声称；索赔\nn. 要求；主张；断言；索赔；权利；要求权；所有权", "1. Opposition leaders will claim victory if the turnout is lower than 50%.\n   如果投票率低于 50%，反对党领袖将宣布获胜。\n2. I don't claim to be a feminist, but I'd like to see more women in top jobs.\n   我不会自称是女权主义者，但我希望看到更多的女性担任高职。", ""},
    {4832, kDeckId, "turmoil", "['tɝmɔɪl]", "n. 混乱；骚动", "1. She lived through the turmoil of the French Revolution.\n   她经历过法国大革命的混乱之后仍旧活着。", ""},
    {4833, kDeckId, "author", "['ɔθɚ]", "n. 作者；创始人", "1. It's clear that the author is a woman.\n   显然，这位作者是女性。\n2. Nothomb is a Belgian author.\n   诺东是位比利时作家。", ""},
    {4834, kDeckId, "greenhouse", "['ɡrinhaʊs]", "n. 温室", "1. What we are seeking, after all, is not simply an agreement to limit greenhouse gas emissions.\n   我们正在寻求的目标毕竟不只是一项限制温室气体排放的协议。\n2. I think each and every one of us is responsible for the greenhouse gases we emit in our daily actions and choices.\n   我认为每一个人都是我们每天的行动和选择中排放的温室气体的责任。", ""},
    {4835, kDeckId, "plus", "[plʌs]", "adj. 正的；加的\nprep. 加上\nn. 加号；正号", "1. Another of the Beach Club's plus points is that it's right in the middle of town.\n   海滩俱乐部的另一个优点是它就位于城中心。\n2. This is not an exciting car to drive, but on the plus side it is extremely reliable.\n   这辆车开起来不刺激，不过从好的方面来说它非常可靠。", ""},
    {4836, kDeckId, "license", "['laɪsns]", "n. 许可证；执照\nv. 准许；认可", "1. Since you have no license, you are not allowed to drive.\n   因为你没有驾驶执照，所以不允许你开车。\n2. To help lower costs, IBM offers flexible virtualization license costs, where you pay only for the number of virtual resources that you have deployed.\n   为了帮助降低成本，IBM 提供灵活的虚拟化许可证费用机制，您只需根据已经部署的虚拟资源数量付费。", ""},
    {4837, kDeckId, "disk", "[dɪsk]", "n. 唱片；圆盘；盘状物", "1. The food processor has thin, medium, and thick slicing discs.\n   这个食品加工机有薄、中、厚的切片盘。", ""},
