    {4839, kDeckId, "favourable", "['feivərəbl]", "adj. 赞许的；有利的；顺利的", "1. The response has been overwhelmingly favorable.\n   回应是一边倒的肯定。\n2. favourable film reviews\n   正面的影评", ""},
    {4840, kDeckId, "somehow", "['sʌmhaʊ]", "adv. 不知怎么地；设法；以某种方式", "1. Maybe we could glue it together somehow or other .\n   也许我们可以想什么办法把它粘起来。\n2. Don't worry, we'll get the money back somehow.\n   别担心，我们总会把那些钱拿回来的。", ""},
    {4841, kDeckId, "brief", "[brif]", "adj. 简短的；简洁的\nn. 简报\nv. 简短介绍；简要汇报", "1. Let's keep this conversation brief; I have a plane to catch.\n   我们长话短说吧，我还要赶飞机。\n2. A Defense Department spokesman briefed reporters.\n   一位国防部发言人向记者们介绍了情况。", ""},
    {4842, kDeckId, "edit", "['ɛdɪt]", "v. 编辑；校订", "1. The newspaper edits letters before printing them.\n   这家报社刊登读者来信前先作校订。", ""},
    {4843, kDeckId, "minus", "['maɪnəs]", "adj. 负的；减的\nprep. 减去\nn. 负号；减号", "1. On the minus side, there is no free back-up service if things go wrong.\n   不足之处是出了问题没有免费的技术支持服务。\n2. 'Any minus points ?' 'Well, the engine is rather noisy.'\n   \"有什么毛病吗？\"\"嗯，发动机噪音很大。\"", ""},
