    {4856, kDeckId, "brace", "[bres]", "v. 使防备；使受锻炼；支撑；使绷紧\nn. 托架；支架", "1. Workers used steel beams to brace the roof.\n   工人用钢梁支撑屋顶。\n2. Wait until we've braced the ladder.\n   等我们把梯子支撑住再说。", ""},
    {4857, kDeckId, "penalty", "['pɛnəlti]", "n. 处罚；惩罚", "1. Withdrawing the money early will result in a 10% penalty.\n   提前支取这笔钱将被处以10%的罚金。\n2. If he is convicted, he could receive the death penalty .\n   一旦定罪，他可能会被判处死刑。", ""},
    {4858, kDeckId, "salient", "['selɪənt]", "adj. 显著的；突出的A", "1. the salient points of the report\n   这份报告的要点", ""},
